A massive blackout plunged Spain and Portugal into chaos—trains halted, hospitals scrambled, supermarkets stripped bare. Officials say the cause is still under investigation, but one thing is clear: modern grids are increasingly fragile. With nations racing to transform their energy systems, have we ignored the risks? This could be more than a one-off failure—it might be a glimpse into the kind of disruption that’s quietly becoming the new normal.
title: Was This a Rehearsal for the Next Global Event?  – SF575
